# JavDB Auto Spider - Cron Job Configuration
# This file defines scheduled tasks for the Docker container
#
# Format Options:
# 1. Standard cron format:
#    MINUTE HOUR DAY MONTH WEEKDAY COMMAND
#    Example: 0 8 * * * python3 pipeline.py
#
# 2. Variable format:
#    CRON_TASKNAME="MINUTE HOUR DAY MONTH WEEKDAY COMMAND"
#    Example: CRON_DAILY="0 8 * * * python3 pipeline.py"
#
# Cron time fields:
#   - MINUTE: 0-59
#   - HOUR: 0-23 (in container timezone, default Asia/Shanghai)
#   - DAY: 1-31
#   - MONTH: 1-12
#   - WEEKDAY: 0-7 (0 and 7 are Sunday)
#
# Common schedule examples:
#   0 8 * * *     - Every day at 8:00 AM
#   0 */6 * * *   - Every 6 hours
#   0 8,20 * * *  - Twice daily at 8:00 AM and 8:00 PM
#   0 8 * * 1-5   - Weekdays at 8:00 AM
#   30 8 * * 0    - Sundays at 8:30 AM

# ============================================================================
# SCHEDULED TASKS
# ============================================================================

# Daily pipeline run at 8:00 AM (default)
CRON_DAILY="0 8 * * * python3 pipeline.py --use-proxy"

# Optional: Run pipeline again at 8:00 PM
# CRON_EVENING="0 20 * * * python3 pipeline.py --use-proxy"

# Optional: Weekly full scan on Sundays (ignore history, scan all pages)
# CRON_WEEKLY="0 3 * * 0 python3 pipeline.py --use-proxy --ignore-history --all"

# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# Pipeline arguments reference:
#   --use-proxy        : Use proxy for requests (configured in config.py)
#   --ignore-history   : Ignore previously parsed movies
#   --all              : Parse all available pages
#   --phase 1          : Run only phase 1 (subtitle entries)
#   --phase 2          : Run only phase 2 (high-rated entries)
#   --dry-run          : Simulate without making changes
#
# You can also run individual scripts:
#   python3 scripts/spider.py [args]
#   python3 scripts/qb_uploader.py [args]
